Cellared 1 Year ------
Aroma - heavy fruit, mild caramel;
Appearance - deep amber, slightly opaque, fluffy head, great lacing;
Taste - complex fruit front, sweet caramel blends into the back, finish has a hoppy tang with a faint alcohol heat;
Palate - quite smooth for the style, excellent body;
Overall - simply stated, the strong ale of which all strong ales are judged.
